main for test runner implementation for TestRegistry tests.

Aeryn supports the ability to register tests in any file using the TestRegistry (singleton) class and it's associated macros. testrunner2 is an example project using TestRegistry and this is its main funtion.

Parameters:
argc An integer that contains the count of arguments that follow in argv. The argc parameter is always greater than or equal to 1.
argv An array of null-terminated strings representing command-line arguments entered by the user of the program.
Returns:
0 if all tests pass, otherwise -1.
